The paper deals with trajectory-centric model-based reinforcement learning for robotic manipulation tasks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also involves optimization techniques for policy synthesis, which could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The problem formulation and solution involve nonlinear programming, which could be categorized under control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of computer vision for some of the tasks, which could be categorized under computer vision (cs.CV).
